OL,3,C'My family was ripped away from me':
OL,4,CMan orphaned by infected blood scandal
OL,6,FIt was told Factor 8 was considered a
OL,7,Fwonder drug in the 1970s because it
OL,8,Fallowed haemophiliacs to inject
OL,9,Fthemselves at home rather than going
OL,10,Fto hospital.
OL,12,FThe plasma-derived product helped
OL,13,Fclotting and curbed the bleeding from
OL,14,Fminor injuries that haemophiliacs
OL,15,Fexperienced.
OL,17,FBut demand was so high that the NHS
OL,18,Fhad to turn to drug companies in the
OL,19,FUnited States for supplies. In the US
OL,20,Fdonations were paid for, attracting
OL,21,Fthose desperate for cash.
